Platform Specialty Products Corporation Key Developments

Blackstone Group Reportedly Advanced In Final Stages With Platform Specialty Products
Jul 24 17
The Blackstone Group L.P. (NYSE:BX) has advanced into the final stages of a $4.25 billion auction for half of Platform Specialty Products Corporation (NYSE:PAH), sources told The Post. Platform Speciality Products is looking to sell the agricultural chemical side of its business, with Blackstone leading a consortium of bidders that’s currently in the lead, sources told the Post. Platform Specialty aims to sign a deal in the next two weeks to sell the division, a source said.


UPL Reportedly Explores Bid For Platform Specialty Agrochem Unit 
Jul 24 17
UPL Limited (BSE:512070) is exploring a bid of more than $4 billion for the agrochemicals business of Platform Specialty Products Corporation, according to people familiar with the matter. UPL is in talks with New Mountain Capital LLC about teaming up on an offer, the sources said.


Blackstone Group Reportedly Eyes Half of Platform Specialty Products
Jun 21 17
The Blackstone Group L.P. (NYSE:BX) is reportedly eying to buy to buy half of Platform Specialty Products Corporation (NYSE:PAH). Blackstone Group has formed a bidding consortium that could shell out more than $4 billion to buy half of Platform Specialty Products, whose biggest shareholder is Bill Ackman, three sources told The Post. “There is a reasonable possibility a deal happens,” a source said.The sale portion is the agriculture chemicals division. Bill Ackman’s remaining Platform Specialty Products would then use the money to retire company debt and buy back stock, a source said. Platform Specialty Products and Blackstone Group did not return calls.


