Business

Investors Catching Stocks Platform Specialty Products Corporation (PAH)

By Adam Smith -  Jul 24, 2017 0 24 









Platform Specialty Products Corporation (PAH) will report its next earnings on Aug 07 BMO. The company reported the earnings of $0.16/Share in the last quarter where the estimated EPS by analysts was $0.14/share. The difference between the expected and actual EPS was $0.02/share, which represents an Earnings surprise of 14.3%.




Many analysts are providing their Estimated Earnings analysis for Platform Specialty Products Corporation and for the current quarter 12 analysts have projected that the stock could give an Average Earnings estimate of $0.19/share. These analysts have also projected a Low Estimate of $0.16/share and a High Estimate of $0.21/share.
In case of Revenue Estimates, 8 analysts have provided their consensus Average Revenue Estimates for Platform Specialty Products Corporation as 933.32 Million. According to these analysts, the Low Revenue Estimate for Platform Specialty Products Corporation is 912.15 Million and the High Revenue Estimate is 949.43 Million. The company had Year Ago Sales of 922 Million.
These analysts also forecasted Growth Estimates for the Current Quarter for PAH to be 18.8%. They are projecting Next Quarter growth of 35.7%. For the next 5 years, Platform Specialty Products Corporation is expecting Growth of 1.65% per annum, whereas in the past 5 years the growth was -4.89% per annum.
Some buy side analysts are also providing their Analysis on Platform Specialty Products Corporation, where 3 analysts have rated the stock as Strong buy, 4 analysts have given a Buy signal, 5 said it’s a HOLD, 0 reported it as Underperform and 0 analysts rated the stock as Sell. (These Recommendations are for the Current Month Only reported by Yahoo Finance.)
When it comes to the Analysis of a Stock, Price Target plays a vital role. Analysts reported that the Price Target for Platform Specialty Products Corporation might touch $16 high while the Average Price Target and Low price Target is $14.82 and $12 respectively.

Platform Specialty Products Corporation closed its last trading session at $12.76 with the gain of 1.57%. The Market Capitalization of the company stands at 3.66 Billion. The Company has 52-week high of $14.37 and 52-week low of $6.85. The stock’s current distance from 20-Day Simple Moving Average (SMA20) is 1.4% where SMA50 and SMA200 are 1.15% and 13.51% respectively. The Company Touched its 52-Week High on 04/27/17 and 52-Week Low on 10/13/16.
The Relative Volume of the company is 1.9 and Average Volume (3 months) is 1.78 million. Platform Specialty Products Corporation P/E (price to earnings) ratio is 48.91 and Forward P/E ratio of 13.49.
The company shows its Return on Assets (ROA) value of 0.7%. The Return on Equity (ROE) value stands at 2.6%. While it’s Return on Investment (ROI) value is 2.8%.




While looking at the Stock’s Performance, Platform Specialty Products Corporation currently shows a Weekly Performance of -0.84%, where Monthly Performance is 5.71%, Quarterly performance is -2.99%, 6 Months performance is 17.07% and yearly performance percentage is 42.89%. Year to Date performance value (YTD perf) value is 32.11%. The Stock currently has a Weekly Volatility of 2.26% and Monthly Volatility of 2.85%.








 
